Light Source Type

Power Source
Corded Electric
  • RGBICW Lighting Effects: Set each LED light bulb to a different color, making the light effects feel more comfortable. It can be used as daily and accent lighting. With up to 100 lumens per light, the color temperature is 2700K.
  • Creative DIY Mode: Choose from 47 scene modes and 16 million colors to illuminate your home with Govee outdoor lights for every occasion. Bring outdoor decorations to life with vibrant colors and help your patio stand out.
  • Smart App & Voice Control: Use Govee Home App or pair with Alexa and Google Assistant to adjust brightness and change colors. Combine 3 ropes of 48ft lights for everyday use. Please note the total length should not exceed 144ft (including adapter).
  • Outdoor Durability: Enjoy outdoor lights, regardless of the weather conditions. With added anti-UV material, the outdoor lights and control box are IP65 waterproof with an IP44 adapter (cannot be immersed in water.)
  • Shatterproof Design for Full Protection: Govee outdoor lights are shatterproof, even when knocked over. These outdoor lights can be used for up to 25,000 hours and work in bad weather conditions from -20 °C to 60 °C.
  • Music Sync Mode: Dance the night away as the outdoor lights for patio react to your songs via the integrated mic. With the patio lights outdoor waterproof don't only hear your music, but live it with beautiful dynamic lighting.
  • Exquisite Outdoor Decor: A fascinating display of colors will appear on the smart LED Bulbs, which elevates your outdoor decoration aesthetic and suitable for holiday gift.

    • Eddie O.
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Control over lights
      Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2024
      Size: 96ft
      This is my 1st purchase of these lights. I purchased a few sets of atomi smart led a few years earlier so I can make a small comparison between those 2 companies. Atomi - heavier lights so they seem more durable. Never had one go out. These hung year round on my front... See more
      This is my 1st purchase of these lights. I purchased a few sets of atomi smart led a few years earlier so I can make a small comparison between those 2 companies.
      Atomi - heavier lights so they seem more durable. Never had one go out. These hung year round on my front porch. With the color themes I could change per season/holiday/event.
      The wire was heavy gauge. Make it good for durability but hanging was more of an issue. Thick like a pencil.
      The app was acceptable given the use but could use improvements. Kind if easy to have a timer or scene setting.
      The biggest issue. Connection to them was and is a pain in the ass. The 1st sets I wad able to connect after calling customer service. Worked great after that. NEEDS the lower wifi band. (2.8 I think it was) the higher band it didn't work. I have extenders and that had the band needed. I moved not long ago and tried to reconnect to the new router. Will not connect no matter what. I've tried everything but calling again.
      Long ago I had an issue and called. The company sent a full set to replace. I just opened to try then out and the bulb housing is smaller. Not able to purchase this lights again made me look at govee. The new set connected immediately when I 1st plugged in. So I have manual sets, all 3 and 1 that works wifi. Pointless.... currently these are unavailable.
      GOVEE - Smaller lightweight bulbs. They are BRIGHT. When I first plugged them in it didn't seem so great. Thats because the default was set to 60%. Nearly blinded myself turning them up.
      The wires are thin. Almost like Christmas lights that were coated with a rubber that made it a little thicker.
      The app. Oh the glorious app. I couldn't believe the control. You can select EACH light and change the color. Plenty of pre programmed scenes. My neighbors must have wondered what was going on since I was playing with the colors and scenes for 30 min and still had more to go. There's a music setting so the sound will trigger the lights to strobe. Someone had fireworks going off so it was a fun time to try.
      The "down side" was the plastic clips to hang the strands. Took a little time and measuring to keep them even. That's also the upside. You can make them short or longer pending preference.

      Given both companies I'd stay with Govee. Price and app were the best parts.
      24 feet of atomi were about $80
      96 feet of Govee was. About $100
      I'll try some more with the govee and edit later should I remember to come back.

      Great Set of Lights for the Money
      Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2024
      Size: 144ft
      I recently purchased the Govee Outdoor String Lights 2 to decorate my home for Christmas, and I'm fairly impressed especially for the money. These lights are bright and vibrant, with customizable RGB colors. I love that each bulb can be individually addressed, allowing... See more
      I recently purchased the Govee Outdoor String Lights 2 to decorate my home for Christmas, and I'm fairly impressed especially for the money. These lights are bright and vibrant, with customizable RGB colors. I love that each bulb can be individually addressed, allowing for a lot of creative possibilities

      Setting up the lights was a breeze. The app is intuitive and easy to navigate, and I had no trouble connecting the lights to my Wi-Fi network. The lights themselves are well-made and feel durable enough to withstand the elements.

      While I'm very happy with these lights overall, there are a couple of minor drawbacks. First, you can only connect a maximum of three strands together before needing an additional control box and power source. This can be a bit limiting if you're trying to cover a large area. Second, even though you can daisy-chain strands, you can't sync multiple separate strands together in the app, which would be a nice feature for creating more unified effects on one house.

      Despite these minor limitations, I would recommend the Govee Outdoor String Lights 2. They're a fantastic choice for anyone looking for bright, versatile, and easy-to-use outdoor lighting. I'm looking forward to using them year-round to see how they hold up over time.

    • RonMexico
      3.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Nice lights, but beware of the length limitation...
      Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2025
      Size: 48ft
      These lights look nice and have a lot of smart features that I really like. The warm white glow is cozy without being too yellow, and the 47 scene modes offer a lot of flexibility for different moods or occasions. Setup through the Govee app was smooth, and it synced with... See more
      These lights look nice and have a lot of smart features that I really like. The warm white glow is cozy without being too yellow, and the 47 scene modes offer a lot of flexibility for different moods or occasions. Setup through the Govee app was smooth, and it synced with Alexa without any hiccups. The build quality feels solid, and the waterproofing has held up well so far through a couple of rainy nights.

      That said, I’m giving this three stars because of a major limitation: the maximum length. You can only connect up to 144 feet total (three sets of 48 feet), which just isn’t enough for some larger patios, fences, or backyards. I didn’t realize this until after I purchased and installed two sets and then tried to add a third — and discovered I was already at the cap. It’s frustrating, especially given how customizable and advanced the rest of the system is. I would have happily bought more if the system allowed it.

      If you only need to cover a smaller area, these lights are a solid option. But if you’re hoping to wrap your entire yard or outdoor space, you’ll probably run into the same limitation. Just something to be aware of before committing.
